hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Imprecision noise referred to force:
   The total noise spectral density of the measured quadrature $Y_{\text{meas}}$ is the sum of the contributions from the output field's imprecision noise and the vacuum noise from the imperfect efficiency:
   $$S_{Y,\text{meas}} = \eta S_{Y, \text{out}, \text{imp}} + (1-\eta) S_{Y,\text{vac}} = \eta(\tfrac{1}{2}) + (1-\eta)(\tfrac{1}{2}) = \tfrac{1}{2}.$$
   The measured signal is $Y_{\text{meas,sig}} = \sqrt{\eta}Y_{\text{out,sig}}$. We define the signal transfer function $H(\omega) \equiv Y_{\text{out,sig}}/F_s = \frac{2g_0\sqrt{\bar n}}{\sqrt\kappa}\,\chi_m(\omega)$.
   The input-referred force imprecision noise, $S_{F,\text{imp}}$, is found by setting the signal-to-noise ratio to 1. The measured signal power is $(\sqrt{\eta} H(\omega))^2 S_{F,\text{imp}} = \eta |H(\omega)|^2 S_{F,\text{imp}}$. The measured noise power is $S_{Y,\text{meas}} = 1/2$. Setting them equal gives:
   $$S_{F,\text{imp}} = \frac{1/2}{\eta|H|^2}
     =\frac{1}{2\eta(4g_0^2\bar{n}/\kappa)|\chi_m|^2}
     =\frac{\kappa}{8\eta g_0^2\bar{n}|\chi_m|^2}.$$
2. Back-action noise:
   $$S_{F,\text{BA}}=\frac{4\hbar^2g_0^2\bar{n}}{\kappa}.$$
3. Total added noise:
   The total force noise is the sum of the imprecision and back-action contributions: $S_F=S_{F,\text{imp}}+S_{F,\text{BA}}$.
   Their product is independent of the photon number $\bar{n}$:
   $$S_{F,\text{imp}}S_{F,\text{BA}}
     =\frac{\kappa}{8\eta g_0^2\bar{n}|\chi_m|^2}\,\frac{4\hbar^2g_0^2\bar{n}}{\kappa}
     =\frac{\hbar^2}{2\eta|\chi_m|^2}.$$
   The total noise is minimized when the two contributions are equal ($S_{F,\text{imp}}=S_{F,\text{BA}}$). The minimum value is:
   $$S_{F,\min}=2\sqrt{S_{F,\text{imp}}S_{F,\text{BA}}}
     =2\sqrt{\frac{\hbar^2}{2\eta|\chi_m|^2}}
     =\frac{\sqrt{2}\,\hbar}{|\chi_m|\sqrt\eta}.$$
4. At resonance, $|\chi_m(\omega_m)|=\frac{1}{m\omega_m\gamma_m}$. Substituting this into the expression for the minimum force noise gives the SQL for this measurement:
   $$S_{F,\min}
     =\frac{\sqrt{2}\,\hbar\,m\,\omega_m\,\gamma_m}{\sqrt\eta}.$$
